parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent no-start condition can cause inconvenience, anxiety, and potentially lead to safety risks, especially in emergency situations where reliable transportation is crucial.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
with no crank
no click

or no response when the key is turned; the dashboard lights and accessories work normally; the vehicle may start after a prolonged period of time (10-15 minutes); the failure is unpredictable and may occur multiple times in a day.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the security passlock system can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience, anxiety, and potentially safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start due to a security passlock system failure; the system may need to be replaced; the failure can be intermittent and unpredictable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical system fire can cause damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: A fire occurs in the cab of the vehicle
specifically in the rear section on the driver's side; the fire may be caused by an electrical malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag System Failure due to Broken Wires in Rear Door
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
the airbag light comes on intermittently
especially in damp or rainy conditions
broken or damaged wires in the rear door
airbag failure to deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to replace recalled Takata airbags can lead to the rupture of the airbag inflator, causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Difficulty in getting a replacement for recalled Takata airbags
inability to obtain a loaner vehicle until the repair is completed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power Assist
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power and power assist can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine shuts off
power steering and power brakes become useless
the vehicle is hard to control
the theft deterrent icon appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The throttle sticks
the vehicle accelerates even after taking the foot off the gas
the engine revs down after hitting the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected shift into 4x4 low gear can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission shifts into 4x4 low gear without warning
the vehicle has difficulty moving forward
the steering becomes difficult.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shift into reverse gear can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The gear shifts from "drive" into "reverse" gear without warning
the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Flow Control Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump flow control module can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of vehicle control, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
difficulty starting the engine
rough engine operation
slowing down to a low speed
and the illumination of the "Service Engine Soon" light.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Flow Control Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump flow control module can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing a crash.
symptoms: The check engine warning light illuminates
the engine may be hard to start
may not start
or may stall
and the vehicle may lose power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accelerator pedal sticking can cause unintended acceleration, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing a crash.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks even when the foot is taken off the pedal
the vehicle continues to accelerate even with the foot off the throttle
and the only way to stop the acceleration is to repeatedly tap the pedal until it releases.
